body_html:
Hi guys,
I've just installed tensorflow using the next command:

python -m pip install --upgrade https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/windows/cpu/tensorflow-0.12.1-cp35-cp35m-win_amd64.whl

My python:
Python 3.5.2 (v3.5.2:4def2a2901a5, Jun 25 2016, 22:18:55) [MSC v.1900 64 bit (AMD64)] on win32

OS: Windows 10 Pro

My code:
import tensorflow as tf
print(dir(tf));
W = tf.Variable(tf.random_uniform([1], -1.0, 1.0))

Result:
['builtins', 'cached', 'doc', 'file', 'loader', 'name', 'package', 'spec', 'tf']
Traceback (most recent call last):
File "C:/Users/Ros/Desktop/Tmp/tensorflow.py", line 1, in
import tensorflow as tf
File "C:/Users/Ros/Desktop/Tmp\tensorflow.py", line 3, in
W = tf.Variable(tf.random_uniform([1], -1.0, 1.0))
AttributeError: module 'tensorflow' has no attribute 'Variable'
